{
  "stem": "1415.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This was our first hiding place, my brother's and mine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But after a day, my brother went out, because he was much, much older than me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he tried to find where the transport was and where they were working, so he could sort of blend in.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But he came back for me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he told me that this is not a good place to hide because they already found a few people and killed them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we-- we found another place, and it was inside a building.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In a wall, there was a-- an opening that was no bigger that my body could fit through, which I was eight years old-- could fit squeezing in.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That hole was this big that I had to squish in, squish in like my shoulders, to get in there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And four people were hidden in there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We just had enough place to-- to just be practically one on top of another, squished, sitting, or-- or-- or almost like just barely sitting.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't know how long we were in there, but [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I don't think we could stay there too long because our bodies were-- we just couldn't take that long of a time to be in those positions.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When-- when we came out of there, we found another place in between-- between big [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] tubes, like it was like-- probably was the-- the boiling place for the bricks, or whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was pipes, big pipes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Must have been.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the opening looked like a kettle opening for like a giant oven- type kettle.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And inside were pipes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we sat on those pipes for a long time.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
